&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The final part of the code is using all the functions created before and using them. By employing a nested for loop to gather all the data, I created two arrays (x and y) in which x appends the win rates of computer 1 for every number of rolls they roll before ending its turn. Then y appends all the values in the list x, which will then go back in the nested for loop as the code will then run again for each roll number for computer. This will thus result in generating 100 win rates for each case (20x20) in which y array appends it.
&lt;img src=&quot;/public/img/result.png&quot; alt=&quot;Image&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
